  <summary>5/14/1987--Introduced.
Surrogacy Arrangements Act of 1987 - Amends the Federal criminal code to provide criminal penalties for anyone who, on a commercial basis, knowingly makes, engages in, or brokers a surrogacy arrangement. Amends the Federal Trade Commission Act to provide criminal penalties for anyone who advertises the availability of such an arrangement.</summary>
